arch:property.oc:show_val: Medium-sized unit. Lots of apparent digestion. Many smaller bones seem acid-etched. Is there lots of dog poop here, or could this be an effect of burial in a manure/trash pile? Larger pieces seem unaffected. Very little carnivore gnaw. Not much identified; seems quite fragmented with sharp edges. A lot of black staining, but color seems pretty uniform, mid-brown. Mostly sheep-size. Sample 77, >4mm, 100% sorted. The material matched the dry sieved, with largely sheep/goat size fragments, and a high degree of digestion. There was less than 5% burning.

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
